message.content:
1. Can you provide specific historical sources or archaeological evidence that support the claim that the burial site of the Alamo dead is located at Mission San Francisco de la Espada?
2. Are there any documented accounts or records that confirm Juan Seguín oversaw the burial of the Alamo dead in 1837 and officiated at the funeral at Mission San Francisco de la Espada on February 25?
3. Is there historical documentation or research that addresses the confusion surrounding the burial site of the Alamo dead over the years and provides insights into why some believe it is located at Mission San Francisco de la Espada?
